  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "These developments have contributed to the rise of an entire subfield, the Digital Humanities (see, for example, Underwood 2019).",
    "While in sociology AI driven-technologies tend to be used as an add-on or supplement to social statistics in quantitative research instead of interpretive analysis (Nelson, 2021), AI and other computational tools are making their way into qualitative research as well (c.f.",
    "Taylor & Stoltz, 2020; Kozlowski et al., 2019; Bodell, Magnusson, & Keuschnigg, 2022).",
    "The adoption of previous technological developments in qualitative research is a testament to the synergy between the human and machine approaches.",
    "For instance, Deterding and Waters (2021) assume that qualitative analyses will be conducted using qualitative data analysis (QDA) software and highlight QDA's utility in flexibly coding interview data, including automated coding and analysis functions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While in sociology AI driven-technologies tend to be used as an add-on or supplement to social statistics in quantitative research instead of interpretive analysis (Nelson, 2021), AI and other computational tools are making their way into qualitative research as well (c.f.",
    "Taylor & Stoltz, 2020; Kozlowski et al., 2019; Bodell, Magnusson, & Keuschnigg, 2022)."
  ]
